Butcher isn't a bad writer at all, but the "smartass private eye" thing has been done a LOT over the years. As a genre it goes back to just after the First World War.

I know that Jim Butcher has gotten fame and fortune by his twist on the genre, to combine it with magic and low fantasy and the lightest sprinkle of cosmic horror. A guy named Glen Cook has been doing a mashup of similar ingredients since the 1980s and is not nearly as well known, despite his writing being of at least equivalent quality.

This may be part of why I find it a bit amusing when fans mash up the Dresden Files with other properties to do fanfiction, some of which has been genuinely disturbing. Reading bad or weird fanfiction is a cheap hobby, but not one I can recommend.
